---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Container from "../../components/Container.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Freestyle Rap — Khonsu Development"
  description="Practice freestyle rap with beats, rhymes, visual inspiration, adjustable tempo, and recording — powered by Double Rhyme."
  canonicalPath="/freestyle-rap"
>
  <section class="py-12 sm:py-16">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="card mb-10 overflow-hidden p-5 sm:p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="h-12 w-12 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl bg-white/10 ring-1 ring-white/10">
              <img
                src="/apps/freestyle/freestyle.png"
                alt="Freestyle Rap app icon"
                class="h-full w-full object-cover"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white">Freestyle Rap</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-zinc-300">Beats • Rhymes • Inspiration • Tempo</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-5 grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10">
              <img
                src="/apps/freestyle/screenshot-1.png"
                alt="Freestyle Rap app screenshot"
                class="h-44 w-full object-cover sm:h-48"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
            <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10">
              <img
                src="/apps/freestyle/screenshot-2.png"
                alt="Freestyle Rap app screenshot"
                class="h-44 w-full object-cover sm:h-48"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <article
          class="prose prose-invert prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-p:text-zinc-200 prose-li:text-zinc-200 max-w-none"
        >
          <h1>Ready for your new rap challenge?</h1>
          <p>
            Up your freestyle rapping game with Freestyle Rap — a simple app to
            learn how to rap freestyle, with inspiration.
          </p>

          <blockquote>
            <p>
              “There’s no reason for somebody who’s good at writing rap to be
              good at freestyling. They’re different parts of your brain. You
              can develop both skills. I’m a much better writer.”
            </p>
            <p>— Daveed Diggs, American actor and rapper</p>
          </blockquote>

          <h2>How it works</h2>
          <h3>1. Choose your favorite beat</h3>
          <p>Purchase your favorite beats in a large library.</p>

          <h3>2. Get ready</h3>
          <p>Decide on a language, a beat, and a tempo.</p>

          <h3>3. Rap your freestyle</h3>
          <p>
            A rhyme and a picture appear on a regular tempo, for you to use as
            inspiration during your freestyle rapping.
          </p>

          <h3>4. Review your recording</h3>
          <p>
            At the end of the beat, review and share your performance — or
            challenge your friends!
          </p>

          <h2>Freestyle rap in 50 languages!</h2>
          <p>
            Afrikaans, Albanian, Arabic, Armenian, Azerbaijani, Basque, Bosnian,
            Bulgarian, Catalan, Chinese, Croatian, Czech, Danish, Dutch,
            English, English (US), Esperanto, Estonian, Finnish, French,
            Georgian, German, Greek, Hindi, Hungarian, Indonesian, Italian,
            Kannada, Korean, Latin, Latvian, Macedonian, Malay, Malayalam,
            Norwegian, Persian (Farsi), Polish, Portuguese, Romanian, Russian,
            Serbian, Slovak, Slovenian, Spanish, Swedish, Tamil, Turkish, Urdu,
            Vietnamese, Welsh
          </p>

          <p>
            Freestyle Rap is powered by <a href="https://double-rhyme.com/"
              >Double Rhyme</a
            >, the rapper’s reference for complex rhyme generation. Rhymes are
            generated by Double Rhyme and are sometimes created and reviewed by
            users.
          </p>

          <p>
            If you found a bug or a content error, please report it to{" "}
            <a href="mailto:khonsu.development@gmail.com"
              >khonsu.development@gmail.com</a
            >.
          </p>
        </article>

        <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
          <a
            class="btn btn-primary"
            href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.lyricspiration.freestyle"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            target="_blank"
          >
            Get it on Google Play
          </a>
          <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/apps">
            Explore all apps
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 text-sm text-zinc-400">
          <a
            class="underline decoration-white/20 underline-offset-4 hover:text-white"
            href="/freestyle-rap/terms-and-conditions-for-freestyle-rap"
          >
            Terms &amp; Conditions for Freestyle Rap
          </a>
          {" · "}
          <a
            class="underline decoration-white/20 underline-offset-4 hover:text-white"
            href="/freestyle-rap/privacy-policy-for-freestyle-rap"
          >
            Privacy Policy for Freestyle Rap
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
